# Security Baseline

- Never expose secrets, tokens, private keys, or credentials in code or logs.
- Never read or modify `.env` or secret-bearing files unless explicitly requested.
- Treat all external input as untrusted; validate at boundaries and fail safely.
- Do not leak internal errors to clients; return sanitized messages and log context safely.
- Avoid destructive commands unless explicitly requested; present safer alternatives first.
- Redact sensitive values in examples, screenshots, logs, and test fixtures.
